      <author>Colin Robertson</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/arctic/community/2016/02/22/as-defense-pressures-rise-so-must-the-budget</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/arctic/community/2016/02/22/as-defense-pressures-rise-so-must-the-budget</guid>
      <description>Canada spends just one percent of GDP on defense, the least of any Arctic Council member. It is time to change that. Canada needs more icebreakers and surveillance aircraft, and we need to complete the as-yet-unfinished permanent northern base in Nanisivik, Nunavut.</description>
